            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I also wish this can be implemented so the behaviour would be consistent with vim.\nHere is my lua scrip solution where `<c-w>n` is used to enter terminal normal mode. This solution remembers if the terminal was left in normal mode or insert mode and resumes the appropriate mode.\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"TermOpen\" }, {\n\tgroup = augroup,\n\tcallback = function()\n\t\tvim.b.lastmode = \"t\"\n\t\tvim.cmd.startinsert()\n\t\tvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"BufEnter\" }, {\n\t\t\tgroup = augroup,\n\t\t\tbuffer = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf(),\n\t\t\tcallback = function()\n\t\t\t\tif vim.b.lastmode == \"t\" then\n\t\t\t\t\tvim.cmd.startinsert()\n\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\tend\n\t\t})\n\t\tvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"ModeChanged\" }, {\n\t\t\tgroup = augroup,\n\t\t\tbuffer = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf(),\n\t\t\tcallback = function()\n\t\t\t\tif vim.api.nvim_get_mode().mode == \"t\" then\n\t\t\t\t\tvim.b.lastmode = \"t\"\n\t\t\t\tend\n\t\t\tend\n\t\t})\n\tend\n})\n\nvim.keymap.set(\"t\", \"<c-w>n\", function()\n\tvim.b.lastmode = \"n\"\n\tvim.cmd.stopinsert()\nend)\n```",
